    Description:
  Creates a boilerplate file for a new Query Object. Pass it a name,
  either CamelCase or snake_case. Optional: a list of methods as arguments.
  To create a Query object within a module, pass it as either `--module NAME`
  or `--module=NAME`.
  The file lives, by community-convention, in `app/queries`, or in
  `app/queries/{module}` if module is present.

Example:
  `rails generate query MostPopularArticles --module frontpage`

  This will create:
    app/queries/frontpage/most_popular_articles_query.rb

